 cabinet and associates\n\nBULLET::::- Rosen, Greg. ed. \"Dictionary of Labour Biography\". (Politicos Publishing, 2002);\nBULLET::::- Morgan, Kenneth O. \"Labour people: leaders and lieutenants, Hardie to Kinnock\" (1987).\nScholarly studies\n\nBULLET::::- Addison, Paul. \"No Turning Back: The Peaceful Revolutions of Post-War Britain\" (2011) excerpt and text search\nBULLET::::- , detailed coverage of nationalisation, welfare state and planning.\nBULLET::::- Crowcroft, Robert, and Kevin Theakston. \"The Fall of the Attlee Government, 1951.\" in Timothy Heppell and Kevin Theakston, eds. \"How Labour Governments Fall\" (Palgrave Macmillan UK, 2013). PP 61–82.\nBULLET::::- Francis, Martin. \"Ideas and policies under Labour, 1945–1951: building a new Britain\" (Manchester UP, 1997).\nBULLET::::- Golant, W. \"The Emergence of CR Attlee as Leader of the Parliamentary Labour Party in 1935.\" \"Historical Journal\" 13#2 (1970): 318–332. in JSTOR\nBULLET::::- Jeffreys, Kevin. \"The Attlee Years, 1935–1955.\" The Labour Party. Palgrave Macmillan UK, 2000. 68-86.\nBULLET::::- Kynaston, David. \"Austerity Britain, 1945–1951\" (2008).\nBULLET::::- Mioni, Michele. \"The Attlee government and welfare state reforms in post-war Italian Socialism (1945–51): Between universalism and class policies.\" \"Labor History\" 57#2 (2016): 277–297. DOI:10.1080/0023656X.2015.1116811\nBULLET::::- Morgan, Kenneth O. \"Labour in Power 1945–1951\" (1984), 564 pp.\nBULLET::::- Ovendale, R. ed., \"The foreign policy of the British Labour governments, 1945–51\" (1984) ·\nBULLET::::- Pugh, Martin. \"\" (2011) excerpt and text search\nBULLET::::- Swift, John. \"Labour in Crisis: Clement Attlee & the Labour Party in Opposition, 1931–1940\" (2001)\nBULLET::::- Tomlinson, Jim. \"Democratic Socialism and Economic Policy: The Attlee Years, 1945–1951\" (2002) Excerpt and text search\nBULLET::::- Weiler, Peter. \"British Labour and the cold war: the foreign policy of the Labour governments, 1945–1951.\" \"Jou