:::- ——— (2005), \"Jack's Life: A Memory of C. S. Lewis\". Broadman & Holman Publishers.\nBULLET::::- William Griffin (2005), \"C. S. Lewis: The Authentic Voice\" (formerly \"C. S. Lewis: A Dramatic Life\"). Lion.\nBULLET::::- Dabney Adams Hart (1984), \"Through the Open Door: A New Look at C. S. Lewis\". University of Alabama Press.\nBULLET::::- Joel D. Heck (2006), \"Irrigating Deserts: C. S. Lewis on Education\". Concordia Publishing House.\nBULLET::::- Carolyn Keefe (1979), \"C. S. Lewis: Speaker & Teacher\". Zondervan.\nBULLET::::- Jon Kennedy (2008), \"The Everything Guide to C. S. Lewis and Narnia\". Adams Media.\nBULLET::::- Jon Kennedy (2012), \"C. S. Lewis Themes and Threads\". Amazon Kindle ASIN B00ATSY3AQ\nBULLET::::- Clyde S. Kilby (1964), \"The Christian World of C. S. Lewis\". Grand Rapids: Eerdmans, 1964, 1995.\nBULLET::::- Don W. King (2001), \"C. S. Lewis, Poet: The Legacy of His Poetic Impulse\". Kent, Ohio: Kent State University Press.\nBULLET::::- Kathryn Lindskoog (1994), \"Light in the Shadowlands: Protecting the Real C. S. Lewis\". Multnomah Pub.\nBULLET::::- Susan Lowenberg (1993), \"C. S. Lewis: A Reference Guide, 1972–1988\". Hall & Co.\nBULLET::::- Wayne Mardindale & Jerry Root (1990), \"The Quotable Lewis\". Tyndale House Publishers.\nBULLET::::- Thomas L. Martin (ed.) (2000), \"Reading the Classics with C. S. Lewis\". Baker Academic.\nBULLET::::- Laura Miller (2008) \"The Magician's Book\", Little, Brown & Co.\nBULLET::::- David Mills (ed) (1998) \"The Pilgrim's Guide: C. S. Lewis and the Art of Witness\". Grand Rapids: Eerdmans.\nBULLET::::- Joseph Pearce (1999), \"C. S. Lewis and the Catholic Church\". HarperCollins, 1999; then Ignatius Press, 2003.\nBULLET::::- Thomas C. Peters (1998), \"Simply C. S. Lewis: A Beginner's Guide to His Life and Works\". Kingsway Publications.\nBULLET::::- Justin Phillips (2003), \"C. S. Lewis at the BBC: Messages of Hope in the Darkness of War\". Marshall Pickering.\nBULLET::::- Harry Lee Poe & Rebecca Whitten Poe (eds) (2006), \"C. S. Lewis Remembered: Collected Reflections of Students, Friends & Colleagues\". Zondervan.\nBULLET::::- Victor Reppert (2003), \"C. S. Lewis's Dangerous Idea: In Defense of the Argument from Reason\". InterVarsity Press.\nBULLET::::- George Sayer (1988), \"Jack: C. S. Lewis and His Times\". London: Macmillan.\nBULLET::::- Peter J. Schakel (1984), \"Reason and Imagination in C. S. Lewis: A Study of \"Till We Have Faces\"\". Grand Rapids: Eerdmans.\nBULLET::::- Peter J. Schakel (2002), \"Imagination and the Arts in C. S. Lewis: Journeying to Narnia and Other Worlds.\" University of Missouri Press.\nBULLET::::- Peter J. Schakel (ed.) (1977), \"The Longing for a Form: Essays on the Fiction of C. S. Lewis\". Kent, Ohio: Kent State University Press.\nBULLET::::- Peter J. Schakel & Charles A. Huttar (eds.) (1991), \"Word and Story in C. S. Lewis\". University of Missouri Press.\nBULLET::::- Stephen Schofield (1983), \"In Search of C. S. Lewis\". Bridge Logos Pub.\nBULLET::::- Jeffrey D. Schultz & John G. West, Jr. (eds) (1998), \"The C. S. Lewis Readers' Encyclopedia\". Zondervan Publishing House.\nBULLET::::- Sanford Schwartz (2009), \"C. S. Lewis on the Final Frontier: Science and the Supernatural in the Space Trilogy\". Oxford University Press. .\nBULLET::::- G. B. Tennyson (ed.) (1989), \"Owen Barfield on C. S. Lewis\". Wesleyan University Press\nBULLET::::- Richard J. Wagner (2005) \"C. S. Lewis and Narnia for Dummies\". For Dummies.\nBULLET::::- Andrew Walker & Patrick James (eds.) (1998), \"Rumours of Heaven: Essays in Celebration of C. S. Lewis\", Guildford: Eagle.\nBULLET::::- Chad Walsh (1949), \"C. S. Lewis: Apostle to the Skeptics\". London: Macmillan\nBULLET::::- Chad Walsh (1979), \"The Literary Legacy of C. S. Lewis\". New York: Harcourt Brace Jovanovich.\nBULLET::::- Michael Ward (2008), \"Planet Narnia\". Oxford University Press.\nBULLET::::- George Watson (ed.) (1992), \"Critical Essays on C. S. Lewis\". Menston: Scolar Pres